  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ConfigKeys
    Interface containing keys for all the properties/attributes referenced from the configuration files.
    ContextKeys
    Interface containing keys for all the attributes stored in the application context
    EnvKeys
    Interface containing keys for all the environment variables that can be used to interact with the application
    ErrorMessageKeys
    Interface containing keys for error messages displayed within the application
    JspViews
    Interface containing keys for all the views (jsp files) used by the application
    RegexPattern
    Interface containing keys for the regex used in restricting field values
    RequestKeys
    Constant Keys for HttpServletRequest attributes
    SessionKeys
    Constant Keys for attributes stored in HttpSession

Package edu.neu.ccis.sms.constants Description

Classes which contains constants like attribute names, request parameter names, etc. which are frequently accessed constant strings across the project.

These classes contain constants used across the project e.g. SessionKeys.java - contains attribute names stored in http session.
